Belief has two different meanings in both English and German. First, belief in the sense of opinion, the unjustified or careless views that someone or a group happens to have. Second, belief in the spirit of belief, or in the idea of the impossibility of virtue. To believe is to believe, in both senses. Only the spirit of truth can be judged as righteous. 

